&lt;h3 id="workflow">Workflow&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>A workflow defines the total flow of data, by describing how nodes are connected between them.
A user can define one or multiple workflows inside a version.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The main components of a workflow are:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>The workflow entrypoint which represents the gRPC service that is tied to the workflow.
This is useful when you define more than one workflow.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>The workflow exitpoint, needed to answer the entrypoint with the requests&amp;rsquo; result.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>The flow shape that links the nodes. Multi-branching is enabled for this version.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>An ordered node list that defines the nodes belonging to the workflow and their specifics.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
